# What is a domain Controller
- A Domain Controller is the brain of a Windows network. 
It authenticates users, enforces rules, and manages everything under the domain, 
ensuring security and consistency across all connected devices.

# What Services can a domain controller give 
- User Authentication
- Centralized Management 
- Authorization
- Group Policy Managemnet 
- Replication

# How I used them in this project

- I used two domain controllers as DNS servers
- You need a backup for redundancy just incase
